        create:     "Design a synthetic gene circuit that expresses a therapeutic protein (e.g. insulin) only when two conditions are simultaneously met: (i) high intracellular glucose (sensor: ChREBP-responsive element); AND (ii) an orally administered small molecule (sensor: tetracycline-responsive TetO element with rtTA). Draw the circuit architecture, label all regulatory elements, specify the promoter design, and explain the AND-gate logic — what happens to insulin expression under each of the four combinations of glucose and drug present/absent."
