        understand: "Explain why the epidermis functions as an effective waterproof barrier despite containing living cells. Your answer must identify the specific layer responsible for waterproofing and describe the molecular mechanism — including the role of lamellar granules.",
        apply:      "A histology slide shows a skin sample with five epidermal strata, including a well-developed stratum lucidum, and a stratum corneum approximately 400 μm thick. (a) Classify the skin as thick or thin. (b) Name two body locations from which this sample could have been taken. (c) Predict whether sebaceous glands and hair follicles will be visible on the same slide — justify your answer.",
        analyze:    "A biopsy from a patient with psoriasis reveals: thickened stratum spinosum (acanthosis), reduced stratum granulosum, parakeratosis (nucleated cells in the stratum corneum), and elongated dermal papillae with dilated capillaries. Analyse each histological finding: identify which step of normal epidermal maturation is disrupted, explain the mechanism, and deduce what drives the elongated papillae and associated skin redness.",
