        evaluate:   "A cosmetics company markets a moisturiser claiming it 'penetrates all epidermal layers to deliver collagen directly to the dermis, repairing deep skin structure.' Evaluate this claim in full: identify the specific barrier mechanism that would resist penetration by a large collagen molecule, state the minimum properties a molecule must have to reach the dermis, and assess whether dermal collagen delivery via a topical cream is scientifically plausible.",
        create:     "Develop a patient education plan for a patient with vitiligo (patchy loss of melanocytes) who asks about sun exposure and vitamin D. Your plan must: (a) explain the normal function of melanocytes and why their absence in vitiligo patches specifically increases UV risk in those areas; (b) address the vitamin D synthesis dilemma for the patient; (c) provide a specific evidence-based sun exposure and supplementation recommendation; (d) explain the relative skin cancer risk in affected vs unaffected skin and which cancer type is of greatest concern."
