        apply:      "A patient has a tidal volume of 450 mL, an anatomical dead space of 150 mL, and a respiratory rate of 20 breaths/min. (a) Calculate minute ventilation. (b) Calculate alveolar ventilation. (c) If the patient's respiratory rate drops to 10 breaths/min but tidal volume increases to 750 mL, recalculate both values and state which breathing pattern is more efficient for gas exchange.",
