        apply:      "An organism has a haploid number of n = 4. (a) Calculate the number of genetically distinct gamete types possible from independent assortment alone. (b) If one pair of homologues undergoes non-disjunction in meiosis I, draw the four resulting gametes and state the chromosome number of each. (c) If one of the n+1 gametes is fertilised by a normal gamete, state the chromosome number of the resulting zygote.",
