        evaluate:   "A student argues that crossing over is more important than independent assortment for generating genetic variation because 'crossing over can produce infinite combinations within a chromosome, whereas independent assortment is limited to 2ⁿ.' Evaluate this argument — identify what is correct, what is incorrect or misleading, and provide a balanced conclusion that specifies the relative contributions of each mechanism.",
        create:     "Construct a fully annotated diagram showing the complete fate of one pair of homologous chromosomes (each with two different alleles on each arm) through all stages of meiosis I and II, including one crossover event in prophase I. Your diagram must show: (a) the allele arrangement on each chromatid before and after crossing over; (b) which chromatids are recombinant; (c) the allele content of all four final haploid cells; (d) an annotation of which cells carry parental vs recombinant genotypes."
